  "prompt": "How do I get the best employment attorney in Los Angeles?",
  "response": "To find the best employment attorney in Los Angeles, consider these steps:\n\n1. Research methods:\n- Check state bar association referral services\n- Use online legal directories (Avvo, FindLaw, Martindale-Hubbell)\n- Read online reviews and ratings\n- Ask for recommendations from professional networks\n\n2. Qualities to look for:\n- Extensive experience in employment law\n- Proven track record of successful cases\n- Specialization in your specific employment issue\n- Strong communication skills\n- Good reputation in the legal community\n\n3. Specific steps:\n- Consult the State Bar of California website\n- Schedule initial consultations with multiple attorneys\n- Ask about their experience with cases similar to yours\n- Inquire about their success rates\n- Discuss fee structures\n- Check their disciplinary record\n\n4. Recommended research sources:\n- Los Angeles County Bar Association\n- California Employment Lawyers Association\n- Super Lawyers directory\n- Yelp and Google reviews\n\n5. Potential top-rated firms:\n- Seyfarth Shaw LLP\n- Littler Mendelson\n- Fisher & Phillips\n- Greenberg Traurig\n\nRemember to verify credentials and interview potential attorneys to find the best fit for your specific situation.",
